<body>

    <h1 style="text-align: center;">Master of Business Administration (MBA)</h1>

    <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            The Master of Business Administration (MBA) is a two-year postgraduate degree program designed to develop leadership and management skills. The course focuses on various aspects of business operations such as marketing, finance, human resources, operations, and entrepreneurship, preparing students for leadership roles in diverse industries.
        </p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Course Highlights</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Duration: 2 years (4 semesters)</li>
            <li>Eligibility: Bachelor's degree in any discipline with a minimum percentage (varies by institution) and qualifying entrance exams like CAT, MAT, GMAT, or XAT</li>
            <li>Focus Areas: Leadership, strategic management, business analytics, and global business</li>
            <li>Specializations: Marketing, Finance, HR, IT, Operations, International Business, and more</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Core Subjects</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Principles of Management</li>
            <li>Financial Management</li>
            <li>Marketing Management</li>
            <li>Human Resource Management</li>
            <li>Business Analytics</li>
            <li>Operations Management</li>
            <li>Entrepreneurship and Innovation</li>
            <li>Strategic Management</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Skills Developed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Leadership and decision-making</li>
            <li>Strategic thinking and problem-solving</li>
            <li>Effective communication and negotiation skills</li>
            <li>Analytical and financial planning</li>
            <li>Team management and organizational behavior</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Career Prospects</h2>
        <p>
            An MBA opens doors to a variety of roles across industries. Common career options include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Business Development Manager</li>
            <li>Marketing Manager</li>
            <li>Financial Analyst</li>
            <li>HR Manager</li>
            <li>Operations Manager</li>
            <li>Management Consultant</li>
            <li>Entrepreneur</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            MBA graduates are also well-suited for leadership roles in multinational corporations, startups, and public sector organizations.
        </p>
    </section>
